Have a look at the code below. What will happen when the `main` method is executed?

```java
class EmptyException extends RuntimeException {
    public EmptyException(String message) {
        super(message);
    }
}

public class Main {
    public static Map<Integer, Integer> removePositives(int[] numbers) {
        Map<Integer, Integer> res = new HashMap<>();
        for (int i = 0; i < numbers.length; i++) {
            if (numbers[i] < 0) {
                res.put(i, numbers[i]);
            }
        }
        if (res.isEmpty()) {
            throw new EmptyException("No elements left!");
        } else {
            return res;
        }
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        removePositives(new int[] {2, 4, 95, 100}); // The array contains only positive numbers
    }
}
```
